## 
# Invalid Endpoint
# 
# This scenario tests how the script handles a malformed or unreachable HASS_API_URL.
# 
# Expected Behavior:
#   - The script logs errors when attempting to reach the invalid URL.
#   - Retries the configured number of times before sending a “down” notification.
#   - Never logs a “recovery” event, as the endpoint remains invalid.
# 
# Test command:
# `../check_endpoint.sh > invalid_endpoint.log 2>&1`
# 
# Verify:
#   1. Logs contain errors for invalid URL resolution:
#     `grep "Failed to connect" invalid_endpoint.log`
#   2. Logs show retries and eventual notification:
#     `grep -E "Retrying|Sending SMS.*API endpoint is invalid" invalid_endpoint.log`
# 
HASS_API_URL="http://invalid-url"
HASS_AUTH_TOKEN="dummy_token"
SMS_TO="+1234567890"
SMS_FROM="sender@example.com"
ENDPOINT_DOWN_MESSAGE="API endpoint is invalid."
ENDPOINT_UP_MESSAGE="API endpoint is back online."
RETRY_COUNT=3
RETRY_INTERVAL=5